{
  "video_id": "Uq6XgrYBugo",
  "title": "Why we have an emotional connection to robots | Kate Darling",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Krystian Aparta"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 13470.0,
      "end_time": 15555.0,
      "text": "There was a day, about 10 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15579.0,
      "end_time": 19523.0,
      "text": "when I asked a friend to hold a baby dinosaur robot upside down."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21889.0,
      "end_time": 25335.0,
      "text": "It was this toy called a Pleo that I had ordered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25359.0,
      "end_time": 29760.0,
      "text": "and I was really excited about it because I&#39;ve always loved robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29784.0,
      "end_time": 32630.0,
      "text": "And this one has really cool technical features."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32870.0,
      "end_time": 34206.0,
      "text": "It had motors and touch sensors"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34230.0,
      "end_time": 36474.0,
      "text": "and it had an infrared camera."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36498.0,
      "end_time": 39260.0,
      "text": "And one of the things it had was a tilt sensor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39285.0,
      "end_time": 41602.0,
      "text": "so it knew what direction it was facing."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42950.0,
      "end_time": 44229.0,
      "text": "And when you held it upside down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44253.0,
      "end_time": 45825.0,
      "text": "it would start to cry."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46527.0,
      "end_time": 50230.0,
      "text": "And I thought this was super cool, so I was showing it off to my friend,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50470.0,
      "end_time": 52852.0,
      "text": "and I said, \"Oh, hold it up by the tail. See what it does.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55268.0,
      "end_time": 58893.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;re watching the theatrics of this robot"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58917.0,
      "end_time": 61116.0,
      "text": "struggle and cry out."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 62767.0,
      "end_time": 64814.0,
      "text": "And after a few seconds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 64837.0,
      "end_time": 66809.0,
      "text": "it starts to bother me a little,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67744.0,
      "end_time": 71168.0,
      "text": "and I said, \"OK, that&#39;s enough now."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 71930.0,
      "end_time": 74235.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s put him back down.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74259.0,
      "end_time": 76814.0,
      "text": "And then I pet the robot to make it stop crying."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 78973.0,
      "end_time": 81425.0,
      "text": "And that was kind of a weird experience for me."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 82840.0,
      "end_time": 86653.0,
      "text": "For one thing, I wasn&#39;t the most maternal person at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 86677.0,
      "end_time": 89408.0,
      "text": "Although since then I&#39;ve become a mother, nine months ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89432.0,
      "end_time": 92865.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;ve learned that babies also squirm when you hold them upside down."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92889.0,
      "end_time": 94452.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95230.0,
      "end_time": 97381.0,
      "text": "But my response to this robot was also interesting"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 97405.0,
      "end_time": 101506.0,
      "text": "because I knew exactly how this machine worked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 101530.0,
      "end_time": 104792.0,
      "text": "and yet I still felt compelled to be kind to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 106450.0,
      "end_time": 109157.0,
      "text": "And that observation sparked a curiosity"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 109181.0,
      "end_time": 112120.0,
      "text": "that I&#39;ve spent the past decade pursuing."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 112911.0,
      "end_time": 114704.0,
      "text": "Why did I comfort this robot?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 116228.0,
      "end_time": 119806.0,
      "text": "And one of the things I discovered was that my treatment of this machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 119831.0,
      "end_time": 123532.0,
      "text": "was more than just an awkward moment in my living room,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 123556.0,
      "end_time": 128976.0,
      "text": "that in a world where we&#39;re increasingly integrating robots into our lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 129000.0,
      "end_time": 132126.0,
      "text": "an instinct like that might actually have consequences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 133452.0,
      "end_time": 137201.0,
      "text": "because the first thing that I discovered is that it&#39;s not just me."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 139249.0,
      "end_time": 144510.0,
      "text": "In 2007, the Washington Post reported that the United States military"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 144750.0,
      "end_time": 147304.0,
      "text": "was testing this robot that defused land mines."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 147329.0,
      "end_time": 150241.0,
      "text": "And the way it worked was it was shaped like a stick insect"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 150265.0,
      "end_time": 152916.0,
      "text": "and it would walk around a minefield on its legs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 152940.0,
      "end_time": 156146.0,
      "text": "and every time it stepped on a mine, one of the legs would blow up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 156170.0,
      "end_time": 159226.0,
      "text": "and it would continue on the other legs to blow up more mines."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 159251.0,
      "end_time": 163370.0,
      "text": "And the colonel who was in charge of this testing exercise"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 163610.0,
      "end_time": 165179.0,
      "text": "ends up calling it off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 165203.0,
      "end_time": 167638.0,
      "text": "because, he says, it&#39;s too inhumane"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 167662.0,
      "end_time": 172178.0,
      "text": "to watch this damaged robot drag itself along the minefield."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 174978.0,
      "end_time": 178875.0,
      "text": "Now, what would cause a hardened military officer"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 178899.0,
      "end_time": 180942.0,
      "text": "and someone like myself"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 180966.0,
      "end_time": 182823.0,
      "text": "to have this response to robots?"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 183537.0,
      "end_time": 186847.0,
      "text": "Well, of course, we&#39;re primed by science fiction and pop culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 186871.0,
      "end_time": 189450.0,
      "text": "to really want to personify these things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 189474.0,
      "end_time": 192262.0,
      "text": "but it goes a little bit deeper than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 192287.0,
      "end_time": 197596.0,
      "text": "It turns out that we&#39;re biologically hardwired to project intent and life"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 197620.0,
      "end_time": 202386.0,
      "text": "onto any movement in our physical space that seems autonomous to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 203214.0,
      "end_time": 206679.0,
      "text": "So people will treat all sorts of robots like they&#39;re alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 206703.0,
      "end_time": 209386.0,
      "text": "These bomb-disposal units get names."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 209410.0,
      "end_time": 211910.0,
      "text": "They get medals of honor."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 211116.0,
      "end_time": 213441.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve had funerals for them with gun salutes."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 214380.0,
      "end_time": 218213.0,
      "text": "And research shows that we do this even with very simple household robots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 218237.0,
      "end_time": 220372.0,
      "text": "like the Roomba vacuum cleaner."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 220396.0,
      "end_time": 221686.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 221711.0,
      "end_time": 224800.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just a disc that roams around your floor to clean it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 224824.0,
      "end_time": 227130.0,
      "text": "but just the fact it&#39;s moving around on its own"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 227154.0,
      "end_time": 229321.0,
      "text": "will cause people to name the Roomba"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 229345.0,
      "end_time": 232527.0,
      "text": "and feel bad for the Roomba when it gets stuck under the couch."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 232551.0,
      "end_time": 234416.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 234440.0,
      "end_time": 237780.0,
      "text": "And we can design robots specifically to evoke this response,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 237804.0,
      "end_time": 241265.0,
      "text": "using eyes and faces or movements"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 241289.0,
      "end_time": 244547.0,
      "text": "that people automatically, subconsciously associate"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 244572.0,
      "end_time": 246592.0,
      "text": "with states of mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 246616.0,
      "end_time": 249909.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s an entire body of research called human-robot interaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 249933.0,
      "end_time": 251759.0,
      "text": "that really shows how well this works."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 251783.0,
      "end_time": 254909.0,
      "text": "So for example, researchers at Stanford University found out"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 254933.0,
      "end_time": 256933.0,
      "text": "that it makes people really uncomfortable"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 256958.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259430.00000000003,
      "text": "when you ask them to touch a robot&#39;s private parts."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 259454.0,
      "end_time": 261574.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 261598.0,
      "end_time": 263621.0,
      "text": "So from this, but from many other studies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 263645.0,
      "end_time": 267868.0,
      "text": "we know, we know that people respond to the cues given to them"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 267892.0,
      "end_time": 269914.0,
      "text": "by these lifelike machines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 269938.0,
      "end_time": 271955.0,
      "text": "even if they know that they&#39;re not real."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 273654.0,
      "end_time": 277710.0,
      "text": "Now, we&#39;re headed towards a world where robots are everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 277734.0,
      "end_time": 280799.0,
      "text": "Robotic technology is moving out from behind factory walls."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 280823.0,
      "end_time": 283835.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s entering workplaces, households."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 283860.0,
      "end_time": 290690.0,
      "text": "And as these machines that can sense and make autonomous decisions and learn"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 290930.0,
      "end_time": 292645.0,
      "text": "enter into these shared spaces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 292669.0,
      "end_time": 295164.0,
      "text": "I think that maybe the best analogy we have for this"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 295189.0,
      "end_time": 297124.0,
      "text": "is our relationship with animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 297523.0,
      "end_time": 301411.0,
      "text": "Thousands of years ago, we started to domesticate animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 301435.0,
      "end_time": 305480.0,
      "text": "and we trained them for work and weaponry and companionship."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 305504.0,
      "end_time": 310489.0,
      "text": "And throughout history, we&#39;ve treated some animals like tools or like products,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 310513.0,
      "end_time": 312686.0,
      "text": "and other animals, we&#39;ve treated with kindness"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 312711.0,
      "end_time": 315789.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ve given a place in society as our companions."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 315813.0,
      "end_time": 319662.0,
      "text": "I think it&#39;s plausible we might start to integrate robots in similar ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 321484.0,
      "end_time": 324580.0,
      "text": "And sure, animals are alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 324604.0,
      "end_time": 325753.0,
      "text": "Robots are not."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 327626.0,
      "end_time": 330205.0,
      "text": "And I can tell you, from working with roboticists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 330230.0,
      "end_time": 333752.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re pretty far away from developing robots that can feel anything."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 335720.0,
      "end_time": 336532.0,
      "text": "But we feel for them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 337835.0,
      "end_time": 339420.0,
      "text": "and that matters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 339660.0,
      "end_time": 342693.0,
      "text": "because if we&#39;re trying to integrate robots into these shared spaces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 342717.0,
      "end_time": 347344.0,
      "text": "we need to understand that people will treat them differently than other devices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 347369.0,
      "end_time": 349213.0,
      "text": "and that in some cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 349237.0,
      "end_time": 352409.0,
      "text": "for example, the case of a soldier who becomes emotionally attached"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 352433.0,
      "end_time": 354480.0,
      "text": "to the robot that they work with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 354504.0,
      "end_time": 357800.0,
      "text": "that can be anything from inefficient to dangerous."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 358551.0,
      "end_time": 360688.0,
      "text": "But in other cases, it can actually be useful"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 360713.0,
      "end_time": 363336.0,
      "text": "to foster this emotional connection to robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 364184.0,
      "end_time": 366318.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re already seeing some great use cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 366342.0,
      "end_time": 368945.0,
      "text": "for example, robots working with autistic children"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 368970.0,
      "end_time": 372604.0,
      "text": "to engage them in ways that we haven&#39;t seen previously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 372628.0,
      "end_time": 376628.0,
      "text": "or robots working with teachers to engage kids in learning with new results."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 377433.0,
      "end_time": 378813.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s not just for kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 379750.0,
      "end_time": 382973.0,
      "text": "Early studies show that robots can help doctors and patients"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 382997.0,
      "end_time": 384424.0,
      "text": "in health care settings."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 385535.0,
      "end_time": 387345.0,
      "text": "This is the PARO baby seal robot."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 387369.0,
      "end_time": 390654.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s used in nursing homes and with dementia patients."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 390678.0,
      "end_time": 392248.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s been around for a while."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 392272.0,
      "end_time": 395597.0,
      "text": "And I remember, years ago, being at a party"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 395621.0,
      "end_time": 398192.0,
      "text": "and telling someone about this robot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 398216.0,
      "end_time": 400342.0,
      "text": "and her response was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 400366.0,
      "end_time": 401628.0,
      "text": "\"Oh my gosh."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 402508.0,
      "end_time": 403695.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s horrible."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 405560.0,
      "end_time": 408453.0,
      "text": "I can&#39;t believe we&#39;re giving people robots instead of human care.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 410540.0,
      "end_time": 412415.0,
      "text": "And this is a really common response,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 412439.0,
      "end_time": 414938.0,
      "text": "and I think it&#39;s absolutely correct,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 414962.0,
      "end_time": 417200.0,
      "text": "because that would be terrible."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 417795.0,
      "end_time": 420279.0,
      "text": "But in this case, it&#39;s not what this robot replaces."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 420858.0,
      "end_time": 423978.0,
      "text": "What this robot replaces is animal therapy"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 424200.0,
      "end_time": 427200.0,
      "text": "in contexts where we can&#39;t use real animals"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 427224.0,
      "end_time": 428392.0,
      "text": "but we can use robots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 428416.0,
      "end_time": 433646.0,
      "text": "because people will consistently treat them more like an animal than a device."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 435502.0,
      "end_time": 437882.0,
      "text": "Acknowledging this emotional connection to robots"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 437906.0,
      "end_time": 439875.0,
      "text": "can also help us anticipate challenges"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 439899.0,
      "end_time": 443350.0,
      "text": "as these devices move into more intimate areas of people&#39;s lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 444111.0,
      "end_time": 447515.0,
      "text": "For example, is it OK if your child&#39;s teddy bear robot"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 447539.0,
      "end_time": 449776.0,
      "text": "records private conversations?"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 449800.0,
      "end_time": 453863.0,
      "text": "Is it OK if your sex robot has compelling in-app purchases?"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 453887.0,
      "end_time": 455283.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 455307.0,
      "end_time": 457808.0,
      "text": "Because robots plus capitalism"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 457832.0,
      "end_time": 461537.0,
      "text": "equals questions around consumer protection and privacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 462549.0,
      "end_time": 464161.0,
      "text": "And those aren&#39;t the only reasons"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 464185.0,
      "end_time": 466755.0,
      "text": "that our behavior around these machines could matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 468747.0,
      "end_time": 472170.0,
      "text": "A few years after that first initial experience I had"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 472410.0,
      "end_time": 474352.0,
      "text": "with this baby dinosaur robot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 474376.0,
      "end_time": 476876.0,
      "text": "I did a workshop with my friend Hannes Gassert."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 476901.0,
      "end_time": 479798.0,
      "text": "And we took five of these baby dinosaur robots"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 479822.0,
      "end_time": 482275.0,
      "text": "and we gave them to five teams of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 482299.0,
      "end_time": 483996.0,
      "text": "And we had them name them"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 484200.0,
      "end_time": 487829.0,
      "text": "and play with them and interact with them for about an hour."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 488707.0,
      "end_time": 490913.0,
      "text": "And then we unveiled a hammer and a hatchet"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 490937.0,
      "end_time": 493215.0,
      "text": "and we told them to torture and kill the robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 493239.0,
      "end_time": 496246.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 496857.0,
      "end_time": 499151.0,
      "text": "And this turned out to be a little more dramatic"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 499175.0,
      "end_time": 500453.0,
      "text": "than we expected it to be,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 500477.0,
      "end_time": 503549.0,
      "text": "because none of the participants would even so much as strike"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 503573.0,
      "end_time": 504880.0,
      "text": "these baby dinosaur robots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 504904.0,
      "end_time": 510540.0,
      "text": "so we had to improvise a little, and at some point, we said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 510780.0,
      "end_time": 514515.0,
      "text": "\"OK, you can save your team&#39;s robot if you destroy another team&#39;s robot.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 514539.0,
      "end_time": 516394.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 516839.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519340.00000000006,
      "text": "And even that didn&#39;t work. They couldn&#39;t do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 519580.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520208.00000000006,
      "text": "So finally, we said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 520232.0,
      "end_time": 522265.0,
      "text": "\"We&#39;re going to destroy all of the robots"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 522289.0,
      "end_time": 524574.0,
      "text": "unless someone takes a hatchet to one of them.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 525586.0,
      "end_time": 529165.0,
      "text": "And this guy stood up, and he took the hatchet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 529189.0,
      "end_time": 531895.0,
      "text": "and the whole room winced as he brought the hatchet down"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 531919.0,
      "end_time": 533699.0,
      "text": "on the robot&#39;s neck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 533723.0,
      "end_time": 540600.0,
      "text": "and there was this half-joking, half-serious moment of silence in the room"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 540850.0,
      "end_time": 541783.0,
      "text": "for this fallen robot."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 541807.0,
      "end_time": 543213.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 543237.0,
      "end_time": 546930.0,
      "text": "So that was a really interesting experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 546955.0,
      "end_time": 549414.0,
      "text": "Now, it wasn&#39;t a controlled study, obviously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 549438.0,
      "end_time": 552288.0,
      "text": "but it did lead to some later research that I did at MIT"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 552312.0,
      "end_time": 554540.0,
      "text": "with Palash Nandy and Cynthia Breazeal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 554564.0,
      "end_time": 558190.0,
      "text": "where we had people come into the lab and smash these HEXBUGs"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 558215.0,
      "end_time": 561302.0,
      "text": "that move around in a really lifelike way, like insects."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 561326.0,
      "end_time": 564460.0,
      "text": "So instead of choosing something cute that people are drawn to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 564484.0,
      "end_time": 566577.0,
      "text": "we chose something more basic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 566601.0,
      "end_time": 570810.0,
      "text": "and what we found was that high-empathy people"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 570105.0,
      "end_time": 572248.0,
      "text": "would hesitate more to hit the HEXBUGS."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 573575.0,
      "end_time": 575139.0,
      "text": "Now this is just a little study,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 575163.0,
      "end_time": 577552.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s part of a larger body of research"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 577576.0,
      "end_time": 580520.0,
      "text": "that is starting to indicate that there may be a connection"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 580544.0,
      "end_time": 582917.0,
      "text": "between people&#39;s tendencies for empathy"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 582941.0,
      "end_time": 584917.0,
      "text": "and their behavior around robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 585721.0,
      "end_time": 589348.0,
      "text": "But my question for the coming era of human-robot interaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 589372.0,
      "end_time": 592426.0,
      "text": "is not: \"Do we empathize with robots?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 593211.0,
      "end_time": 596131.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s: \"Can robots change people&#39;s empathy?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 597489.0,
      "end_time": 599776.0,
      "text": "Is there reason to, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 599800.0,
      "end_time": 602132.0,
      "text": "prevent your child from kicking a robotic dog,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 603228.0,
      "end_time": 606141.0,
      "text": "not just out of respect for property,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 606166.0,
      "end_time": 609119.0,
      "text": "but because the child might be more likely to kick a real dog?"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 610507.0,
      "end_time": 612390.0,
      "text": "And again, it&#39;s not just kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 613564.0,
      "end_time": 617620.0,
      "text": "This is the violent video games question, but it&#39;s on a completely new level"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 617644.0,
      "end_time": 622404.0,
      "text": "because of this visceral physicality that we respond more intensely to"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 622428.0,
      "end_time": 623975.0,
      "text": "than to images on a screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 625674.0,
      "end_time": 628252.0,
      "text": "When we behave violently towards robots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 628276.0,
      "end_time": 631396.0,
      "text": "specifically robots that are designed to mimic life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 631420.0,
      "end_time": 635312.0,
      "text": "is that a healthy outlet for violent behavior"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 635336.0,
      "end_time": 637880.0,
      "text": "or is that training our cruelty muscles?"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 639511.0,
      "end_time": 640661.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t know ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 642622.0,
      "end_time": 646567.0,
      "text": "But the answer to this question has the potential to impact human behavior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 646591.0,
      "end_time": 649359.0,
      "text": "it has the potential to impact social norms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 649383.0,
      "end_time": 653232.0,
      "text": "it has the potential to inspire rules around what we can and can&#39;t do"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 653256.0,
      "end_time": 654406.0,
      "text": "with certain robots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 654431.0,
      "end_time": 656279.0,
      "text": "similar to our animal cruelty laws."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 657228.0,
      "end_time": 660920.0,
      "text": "Because even if robots can&#39;t feel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 660116.0,
      "end_time": 663196.0,
      "text": "our behavior towards them might matter for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 664889.0,
      "end_time": 667744.0,
      "text": "And regardless of whether we end up changing our rules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 668926.0,
      "end_time": 672482.0,
      "text": "robots might be able to help us come to a new understanding of ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 674276.0,
      "end_time": 676592.0,
      "text": "Most of what I&#39;ve learned over the past 10 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 676616.0,
      "end_time": 678854.0,
      "text": "has not been about technology at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 678878.0,
      "end_time": 681381.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s been about human psychology"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 681405.0,
      "end_time": 684700.0,
      "text": "and empathy and how we relate to others."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 685524.0,
      "end_time": 687889.0,
      "text": "Because when a child is kind to a Roomba,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 689262.0,
      "end_time": 693276.0,
      "text": "when a soldier tries to save a robot on the battlefield,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 693301.0,
      "end_time": 696939.0,
      "text": "or when a group of people refuses to harm a robotic baby dinosaur,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 698248.0,
      "end_time": 701439.0,
      "text": "those robots aren&#39;t just motors and gears and algorithms."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 702501.0,
      "end_time": 704406.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re reflections of our own humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 705523.0,
      "end_time": 706674.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 706698.0,
      "end_time": 710950.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}